Usage: comparePinAssignStatistics [-help] [-outFile <qor_compare_file_name>]
                                  -reference <pin_qor_reference_file_name>
                                  -target <pin_qor_target_file_name> [ -ignoreMinWireLength <min_wire_length> ]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-ignoreMinWireLength <min_wire_length> # If reference wire length at a
                                       # partition pin is less than
                                       # min_wire_length, then it will not be
                                       # reported in output file. Default: 60
                                       # microns (string, optional)
-outFile <qor_compare_file_name>       # pin QoR comparison will be output in
                                       # this file. Default: ./qor_compare.txt
                                       # (string, optional)
-reference <pin_qor_reference_file_name>
                                       # pin QoR reference file generated by
                                       # reportPinAssignStatistics command.
                                       # (string, required)
-target <pin_qor_target_file_name>     # pin QoR target file generated by
                                       # reportPinAssignStatistics command.
                                       # (string, required)